v2.0.0
* MAJOR ARCHITECTURAL REVOLUTION:
  + Unified all inference methodologies under a strict R6 class hierarchy, centered on the abstract `SeqDesignInference` base.
  + Implemented a dual-strategy pooling framework for all KK matching-on-the-fly designs:
    - IVWC (Inverse-Variance Weighted Combination): Rigorous variance-weighted pooling of independent matched-pair and reservoir estimators.
    - Combined Likelihood: Joint modeling across the entire dataset using design-aware constraints and efficient likelihood aggregation.
  + Standardized class naming conventions (e.g., `...IVWC`, `...CombinedLikelihood`) for clear API navigation.
  + Hidden all internal abstract base classes from the public R help system to simplify user discovery.

* STATISTICAL METHODOLOGY BREAKTHROUGHS:
  + Zhang (2026) Exact Inference: Full implementation of the exact test-inversion algorithm for distribution-free inference in incidence (log-odds) and quantile regression (median shifts).
  + Survival & Count Advancements:
    - Achieved package-wide unit consistency by standardizing all survival effects to Accelerated Failure Time (AFT) log-time ratios.
    - Added Shared Gamma Frailty models (via `parfm`) for parametric handling of matched-pair dependencies.
    - Added Stratified Cox Proportional Hazards regression for strata-aware survival analysis.
    - Added LWA-style marginal Cox inference for KK designs under both IVWC and Combined Likelihood pooling.
    - Added Clayton-copula paired survival models for KK designs under both IVWC and Combined Likelihood pooling.
    - Added semiparametric transformation models for survival with dependent censoring.
    - Implemented Conditional Poisson regression for exact matched-pair count inference.
    - Added KK hurdle-Poisson count inference under both IVWC and Combined Likelihood pooling, combining matched-pair and reservoir information.
    - Added Restricted Mean Survival Time (RMST) difference with robust SEs.
    - Added Gehan-type rank-based AFT models (via `aftgee`).
  + Added a standalone log-rank inference class with C++ score/variance helpers plus automatic stratification helper logic (`compute_survival_strata_ids_cpp`).
  + Continuous outcomes: added Lin (2013)-style adjusted estimators, robust M-estimation (`MASS::rlm`), and quantile regression support for both non-KK and KK designs, with KK support available under IVWC and Combined Likelihood pooling where appropriate.
  + Incidence outcomes:
    - Added modified Poisson risk-ratio estimators for both non-KK and KK designs.
    - Added marginal standardization / g-computation estimators for both risk differences and risk ratios in non-KK and KK designs.
    - Added Miettinen-Nurminen and Newcombe risk-difference inference.
    - Added log-binomial regression for adjusted risk ratios.
    - Added binomial identity-link regression for adjusted risk differences.
  + Proportion outcomes:
    - Added fractional-logit inference.
    - Added zero/one-inflated beta regression.
  + Extended the Wang & Rosenberger-style randomization confidence interval inversion to ordinal GLM estimators (cumulative logit/probit, adjacent-category, etc.), so computed intervals now use the permutation distribution of their shared treatment parameter.
  + Added zero-inflated negative binomial, hurdle negative binomial, and denominator-aware Poisson/quasi-Poisson inference with new Rcpp solvers for fast score/variance extraction.
  + Ordinal:
    - Added cumulative probit, adjacent-category logit, stereotype logit, stereotype probit, ridit, paired sign, and Jonckheere-Terpstra inference.
    - Added partial proportional-odds estimators that allow covariates to vary across thresholds while still estimating a parallel treatment effect, reusing the stacked design with `fast_logistic_regression_with_var_cpp` so the estimator works on every sequential design (no CRD-only restriction).
    - Added conditional ordinal KK estimators for proportional-odds, continuation-ratio, and adjacent-category formulations.
    - Added ordinal KK mixed-model inference with both logit and probit links, including multivariate CLMM support.
  + Robust & Non-parametric Expansion:
    - Integrated R-estimation (Wilcoxon regression) via `Rfit`, with robust fallback to classical ranks for univariate cases.
    - Full Quantile Regression support (via `quantreg`) within the Compound/IVWC framework.
    - Comprehensive GEE and GLMM support for all response types, utilizing `glmmTMB` for superior random-effects stability.

* EXTREME PERFORMANCE OPTIMIZATION:
  + Developed a suite of high-performance C++ IRLS (Iteratively Reweighted Least Squares) solvers for Logistic, Beta, and Negative Binomial regression.
  + Extended the C++ solver suite to constrained binomial fits for both log-binomial and identity-link binomial regression, plus fast helpers for ordinal g-computation, Jonckheere-Terpstra exact distributions, ridit analysis, and KK hurdle grouping / cluster setup.
  + Leveraged OpenMP and RcppEigen to achieve orders-of-magnitude speedups in bootstrap and randomization distribution computations.
  + Implemented intelligent thread-control for `glmmTMB` to prevent resource contention in parallelized inference loops.
  + Integrated `fixest::feglm.fit` for lightning-fast fixed-effects estimation.

* PRODUCTION-GRADE RELIABILITY:
  + Automated missing data pipeline with Design-aware imputation using `missRanger` and `missForest`.
  + Fully validated support for unequal allocation (prob_T != 0.5) across all 40+ inference classes.
  + Hardened error handling for perfect separation, small-sample degeneracy, and non-convergence.
  + Reworked randomization-test caching so expensive treatment-assignment draws are reused across repeated p-value and CI inversion calls, including custom randomization statistics.
  + Fixed Rd generation issues, removed links to undocumented abstract classes, and aligned file / class naming across refactored ordinal and incidence inference families.
  + Global codebase cleanup: standardized tab-based indentation, fixed all Roxygen warnings, and cleaned up the NAMESPACE.

v1.1.0 (planned)
* Support for unequal allocation (the probability of allocation to treatment and control are not 50-50)
* Support for inverting randomization tests to create nonparametric confidence intervals
* Support for KK simple and regression estimators (that use a linear combination of matches and reservoir estimators) for incidence, count, proportion and survival response types for equal and unequal allocation experiments
* Support for the count response with censoring
* Support for Aalen additive regression model for censored data

v1.0.0
* Support for general response types: 
  + incidence - uses logistic regression via glm to compute weights and perform inference
  + proportion - uses beta regression via betareg::betareg to compute weights and perform inference
  + count (uncensored) - uses negative binomial regression via MASS::glm.nb to compute weights and perform inference
  + survival (censored and uncensored) - uses the median difference via Kaplan-Meier, the Weibull model and the coxph model via the survival package to compute weights and perform inference 
* Weights in KK21 designs now are computed from absolute test statistic values (in v0.1.0 it was based on Rsq which does not generalize to the other response types)
* Support for adding responses whenever they become recorded
* Support for general data frames which include factors, characters, logical data types 
* p does not need to be declared when initializing a design (but n is required still)
* No need to declare factors' levels from the getgo
* Support for missing data imputed via the missRanger and missForest packages
* Support for different feature sets for each subject due to this imputation support
* Additional inference support for parameter / estimator by response types:
  + continuous
    - for KK designs only: additive treatment effect / OLS with covariates and dummies for reservoir and pairs
    - for KK designs only: additive treatment effect / OLS with covariates and random effects for reservoir and pairs
  + incidence
    - probability difference / simple difference in means
    - additive effect on log odds of probability of positive outcome / logistic regression estimate without covariates
    - additive effect on log odds of probability of positive outcome / logistic regression estimate with covariates linear in log odds
    - for KK designs only: additive effect on log odds of probability of positive outcome / OLS with covariates and dummies for reservoir and pairs
    - for KK designs only: additive effect on log odds of probability of positive outcome / OLS with with covariates linear in log odds and random effects for reservoir and pairs
  + proportion
    - expected proportion difference / simple difference in means
    - additive effect on log odds of expected proportion / beta regression estimate without covariates
    - additive effect on log odds of expected proportion / beta regression estimate with covariates linear in log odds    
    - for KK designs only: additive effect on log odds of proportion / beta regression estimate with covariates and dummies for reservoir and pairs
  + count
    - expected mean difference / simple difference in means
    - additive effect on log expected mean difference / negative binomial regression estimate without covariates
    - additive effect on log expected mean difference / negative binomial regression estimate with covariates linear in log odds    
    - for KK designs only: additive effect on log expected mean difference / negative binomial regression estimate with covariates and and dummies for reservoir and pairs
    - for KK designs only: additive effect on log expected mean difference / negative binomial regression estimate with covariates linear in log odds and random effects for reservoir and pairs
  + survival
    - expected median difference / difference of Kaplan-Meier median estimators which uses the controlTest package to compute its sample std error
    - expected restricted mean difference / see survival package for details
    - additive effect on log mean survival / Weibull regression estimate without covariates
    - additive effect on log mean survival / Weibull regression estimate with covariates linear in log mean
    - additive effect on log hazard / Coxph regression estimate without covariates
    - additive effect on log hazard / Coxph regression estimate with covariates linear in log mean
    - additive effect on log hazard / Coxph regression estimate with covariates linear in log mean with covariates and dummies for reservoir and pairs
    - additive effect on log hazard / Coxph regression effect with covariates linear in log mean with covariates and random effects for reservoir and pairs
    
v0.1.0
* Initial Release with support for continuous response type and equal allocation (50-50 treatment/control) only
* Support for designs CRD, BCRD, Atkinson, KK14, KK21, KK21stepwise 
* Support for the following parameter estimation / via estimator:
    - additive treatment effect / simple difference of sample means
    - additive treatment effect / OLS estimator with covariates
    - for KK designs only: additive treatment effect / combined simple difference in means for reservoir and pairs
    - for KK designs only: additive treatment effect / combined OLS for reservoir and pairs
